    "url": "https://lists.nycbug.org/pipermail/talk/2026-April/018894.html",
    "heat": "8 points",
    "time": "13 hours ago",
    "content": "the BSDs in the AI Age the BSDs in the AI Age George Rosamond george at ceetonetechnology.com Thu Apr 2 09:14:11 EDT 2026 Previous message (by thread): NYC*BUG Tonight: Michael W Lucas Next message (by thread): the BSDs in the AI Age Messages sorted by: [ date ] [ thread ] [ subject ] [ author ] I want to initiate a thread on the \"BSDs and AI today.\" A few things first. There are many levels to this discussion, and for the sake of clarity and sanity, please top posting. All replies should be inline. This is useful: https://subspace.kernel.org/etiquette.html#do-not-top-post-when-replying I'm looking to do a presentation on this in the summer for NYC*BUG. There hasn't been anything in our community which provides the high-level overview of the impact of AI, covering things from the impact on the BSD operating systems to the impact on $job, etc. Hopefully this thread can provide some raw materials, and become an outlet for individual experiences and more general views. I initiated a similar fruitful (but private) discussion for another open-source project, and think it's high-time for us to do the same on a public list. *** There's a few layers to this discussions. Note these are discussions points, not \"Yes\" or \"No\" surveys. * How are LLMs (big tech or otherwise) impacting $job now? Are you using Claude Code or similar tools for day to day? Was it required or was it your choice? Was there expectations from this tools in terms of productivity, etc? This question raises the impact of AWS Bedrock/Kiro... * Should BSD projects have explicit LLM-focused policies? Look at the 2nd point in the NetBSD \"Commit Guidelines\" at https://www.netbsd.org/developers/commit-guidelines.html. OSS-Security already discussed the issue with alleged CVEs discovered by people with LLMs trying to stack their resume with credentials. * How should the BSD projects themselves be using LLMs? Integration in the shell (oh, please no...)? Porting of APIs for big tech LLMs? Utilizing LLMs to discover bad code, CVEs, undiscovered vulnerabilities? * How should individual developers and users consider LLMs as tools for contributing to the BSDs and other open-source projects? I happily used a big tech LLM to deal with an rc file for some very Linuxey software wrapped up in systemd clutter. Other relevant questions added to this thread are welcomed, including references to other relevant public mailing list discussions. g Previous message (by thread): NYC*BUG Tonight: Michael W Lucas Next message (by thread): the BSDs in the AI Age Messages sorted by: [ date ] [ thread ] [ subject ] [ author ] More information about the talk mailing list",
    "title_zh": "AI时代的BSD系统",
    "summary_zh": "本文是George Rosamond在邮件列表中发起的一个关于“BSD与AI时代”的讨论线程，旨在为计划在NYC*BUG进行的演讲收集素材。讨论旨在从高层次概述AI对BSD操作系统及相关工作的影响，并汇集个人经验与普遍观点。，讨论围绕几个核心层面展开，均为开放性问题而非简单的是非调查：，首先，探讨大型语言模型（如Claude Code等）如何影响当前工作。问题包括开发者是否在日常工作中使用这些工具、是自愿选择还是被要求使用、以及对生产率的预期如何。此问题也关联到AWS Bedrock/Kiro等服务的影响。，其次，讨论BSD项目是否应制定明确的LLM相关政策。文中以NetBSD的“提交指南”为例，并提及OSS-Security已讨论过由LLM发现潜在CVE（常见漏洞与暴露）可能带来的简历镀金问题。，第三，探讨BSD项目自身应如何利用LLM。可能方向包括：是否将LLM集成到shell中（作者对此表示担忧）、是否为大型科技公司的LLM移植API、以及是否利用LLM来发现不良代码、CVE或未披露的漏洞。，最后，探讨个体开发者和用户如何将LLM视为贡献BSD及其他开源项目的工具。作者分享了自己曾使用某大型科技公司的LLM来处理包裹在systemd杂乱配置中的、具有浓厚Linux风格的软件的rc文件的经验。，讨论欢迎补充其他相关问题及相关公开邮件列表的引用。整体而言，该线程旨在启动一场关于AI时代下BSD生态系统如何适应与利用新技术的公开、建设性对话。"
